============================================================
  DISEASES & MEDICINE
============================================================

Disease:     Tuberculosis
Type:        Bacterial
Pathogen:    M. tuberculosis
Transmission:Airborne droplets
Symptoms:    Persistent cough, night sweats
Treatment:   6-9 month antibiotics
Deaths/yr:   1.6M
Vaccine:     Yes (BCG, partial)
Discovered:  1882

Disease:     HIV/AIDS
Type:        Viral
Pathogen:    HIV
Transmission:Sexual contact, blood
Symptoms:    Flu-like; then AIDS symptoms
Treatment:   Antiretroviral therapy (ART)
Deaths/yr:   0.65M
Vaccine:     No (in development)
Discovered:  1983

Disease:     Dengue
Type:        Viral
Pathogen:    Dengue virus
Transmission:Aedes mosquito
Symptoms:    Fever, severe joint pain, rash
Treatment:   Supportive care, fluids
Deaths/yr:   0.04M
Vaccine:     Yes (for previously infected)
Discovered:  1779

